# Project Report: Two Team Scoreboard

## Introduction
This project simulates a digital scoreboard system used in sports.

## Objective
To design a system that tracks scores of two teams using microcontroller-based architecture.

## Components
- Arduino Uno
- MAX7219 Display
- Push Buttons
- Buzzer

## System Design

### Input
Buttons are used to increment scores.

### Processing
Arduino processes inputs and updates score variables.

### Output
Scores are displayed on 7-segment display.

## Features
- Score tracking
- Countdown timer
- Game over detection
- Buzzer alert
- Winner blinking display

## Conclusion
The project successfully demonstrates an embedded system for real-time score tracking.
